Package: RNAPeaks
Type: Package
Title: RNA-Binding Protein Peak Visualization and Analysis  
Version: 1.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Krushna", "Bhanushali",
           email = "Krushna.Bhanushali@unc.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Gilbert", "Giri",
           email = "Ggiri@unc.edu",
           role = c("aut")))
Description: Creates publication-quality visualizations of RNA-binding protein
    (RBP) peaks overlaid on gene structures derived from Ensembl GTF annotations.
    Key features include single-gene visualization with PlotGene(), multi-gene
    genomic region plots with PlotRegion(), splicing maps that quantify RBP
    binding frequency around exon-intron boundaries with createSplicingMap(),
    and position-specific sequence motif frequency analysis with full IUPAC
    ambiguity code support via createSequenceMap(). Statistical significance is
    assessed using bootstrap-based z-score testing. Includes
    curated sample datasets for immediate exploration.
